.TH "phy_attach_direct" 9 "phy_attach_direct" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_attach_direct \- attach a network device to a given PHY device pointer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phy_attach_direct
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ","
.BI "phy_interface_t interface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
network device to attach
.IP "phydev" 12
Pointer to phy_device to attach
.IP "flags" 12
PHY device's dev_flags
.IP "interface" 12
PHY device's interface
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called by drivers to attach to a particular PHY
device. The phy_device is found, and properly hooked up
to the phy_driver.  If no driver is attached, then a
generic driver is used.  The phy_device is given a ptr to
the attaching device, and given a callback for link status
change.  The phy_device is returned to the attaching driver.
This function takes a reference on the phy device.
